boolean

primer, ch.3; modern, ch.3

since C99
defined in [stdbool.h]
no specific printf-specifier for bools (use e.g. %d instead)

false == 0, true == 1
    - 0 represents logical false
    - any value different from 0 represents logical true

EXAMPLE
#include <stdbool.h>

bool x = true;
printf(!x ? "true" : "false"); // false
